main event: Multiple reports of unidentified aerial objects observed in the Medina, New York area in August 1962.
interesting points: On August 17, 1962, residents reported seeing small objects fall from the sky during a rainfall, which were later sent to the U.S. Air Force for examination.
On August 27, 1962, an object or objects were observed moving slowly overhead from east to west, then turning and moving off westward.
On August 22, 1962, two witnesses observed a circular, luminous object making a 90-degree turn and disappearing from sight.
The objects were described as round, bright, and making a humming sound, with some moving at high speeds and making sharp turns.
The U.S. Air Force and NASA were involved in investigating and responding to these UFO reports from the Medina, New York area.
sighted object: Unidentified aerial objects, including circular, luminous objects and small objects that fell from the sky
witnesses: Multiple civilian residents of Medina, New York
photographs: Yes, the report includes a photograph of an unidentified aerial object, but it is described as grainy and low-quality.
